name: Caterpie
flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Metapod
flavorText: Its shell is filled with its soft innards. It doesn't move much because of the risk it might carelessly spill its innards out.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.

name: Butterfree
flavorText: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Paras
flavorText: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

name: Parasect
flavorText: The large mushroom on its back controls it. It often fights over territory with Shiinotic.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. If 1 of them is heads, this attack does 20 more damage. If 2 of them are heads, this attack does 60 more damage. If all of them are heads, this attack does 120 damage.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Pinsir
flavorText: One solid blow from its horns is enough to split apart a large tree. Its greatest rival in Alola is Vikavolt.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, put your opponent's Active Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your opponent's hand.

name: Surskit
flavorText: When this Pokémon senses danger, a sweet fluid oozes from the tip of its heads. The taste of it disgusts bird Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Masquerain
flavorText: Its wings and antennae don't cope well with moisture. After a rain, it faces sunward to dry off.
Attack1Text: Move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Rowlet
flavorText: This wary Pokémon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

name: Dartrix
flavorText: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Decidueye
flavorText: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Decidueye-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Put 3 cards from your discard pile into your hand. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Grubbin
flavorText: They often gather near places frequented by electric Pokémon in order to avoid being attacked by bird Pokémon.

name: Fomantis
flavorText: They give off a sweet and refreshing scent. Cutiefly often gather near the tall grass where Fomantis are hiding.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Lurantis-GX
Attack1Text: Attach 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Morelull
flavorText: As it drowses the day away, it nourishes itself by sucking from tree roots. It wakens at the fall of night, wandering off in search of a new tree.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Shiinotic
flavorText: It emits flickering spores that cause drowsiness. When its prey succumb to sleep, this Pokémon feeds on them by sucking in their energy.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Grass Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Bounsweet
flavorText: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Steenee
flavorText: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird Pokémon, this Pokémon is totally fine.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Tsareena
flavorText: Its long, striking legs aren't just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may have your opponent reveal their hand. Then, discard a card from it.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage and remove all Special Conditions from this Pokémon.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It's both clever and loyal, but if a stranger tries to invade its territory, it barks threateningly.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Arcanine
flavorText: Overflowing with beauty and majesty, this strong Pokémon appears in ancient Eastern folklore.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Discard 3 Fire Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Torkoal
flavorText: Coal is the source of Torkoal's energy. Large amounts of coal can be found in the mounts where they live.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Litten
flavorText: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

name: Torracat
flavorText: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this Pokémon spits fire.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Incineroar
flavorText: This Pokémon has a violent, selfish disposition. If it's not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainer's orders with complete nonchalance.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

name: Incineroar-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your Benched Fire Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.

name: Psyduck
flavorText: As a result of headaches so fierce they cause it to cry, it sometimes uses psychokinesis without meaning to.
Attack1Text: Both Active Pokémon are now Confused.

name: Golduck
flavorText: It is said that the red part of its forehead grants supernatural powers to those who posses one, so it was over-hunted in the past.
Attack2Text: Discard up to 2 Water Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Poliwag
flavorText: It's still not very good at walking. Its Trainers should train this Pokémon to walk every day.
Attack2Text: This attack does 10 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Poliwhirl
flavorText: It marches over the land in search of bug Pokémon to eat. Then it takes them underwater so it can dine on them where it's safe.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Poliwrath
flavorText: Its percentage of body fat is nearly zero. Its body is entirely muscle, which makes it heavy and forces its swimming prowess to develop.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is affected by a Special Condition, this attack does 80 more damage. Then, remove all Special Conditions from that Pokémon.

name: Shellder
flavorText: The hardness of its shell surpasses the hardness of a diamond. In days gone by, people used the shells to make shields.

name: Cloyster
flavorText: Its hard shell cannot be shattered—not even by a bomb. The contents of the shell remain unknown.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage. If tails, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Lapras-GX
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Corsola
flavorText: Pursued by Mareanie for the branches on its head, this Pokémon will sometimes snap its own branches off as a diversion while it escapes.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Wingull
flavorText: Fishermen keep an eye out for Wingull in the sky, because wherever they're circling, the ocean sure to be is teeming with fish Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon. It can't retreat during your next turn.

name: Pelipper
flavorText: Gathering food is the work of young males. They store food in their capacious beaks and carry it back to others waiting in the nest.
Attack1Text: Put 1 of your Benched Pokémon and all cards attached to it into your hand.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing. If heads, prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn.

name: Popplio
flavorText: This Pokémon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. It's famous for being a hard worker.

name: Brionne
flavorText: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards it enemies.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Primarina
flavorText: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learning from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Primarina-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Water Energy attached to your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Crabominable
flavorText: It just throws punches indiscriminately. In times of desperation, it can lop off its own pincers and fire them like rockets.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Wishiwashi
flavorText: When it's in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may discard all cards attached to this Pokémon and return it to your hand. You can't use this Ability during your first turn or on the turn this Pokémon was put into play.

name: Dewpider
flavorText: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Araquanid
flavorText: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small Pokémon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.
Ability1Text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Fire Pokémon.

name: Pyukumuku
flavorText: It lives in shallow seas, such as areas near a beach. It can eject its internal organs, which it uses to engulf its prey or battle enemies.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, put 6 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Bruxish
flavorText: It stuns its prey with psychokinesis and then grinds them to mush with its strong teeth. Even Shellder's shell is no match for it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Chinchou
flavorText: It lives in the depths beyond the reach of sunlight. It flashes lights on its antennae to communicate with others of its kind.
Attack1Text: Look at 1 of your face-down Prize cards.

name: Lanturn
flavorText: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any Water Energy attached to it, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Charjabug
flavorText: From the food it digests, it generates electricity, and it stores this energy in its electric sac.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Vikavolt
flavorText: It produces electricity via an electrical organ in its abdomen. It overwhelms bird Pokémon with shocking beams of electrical energy.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Grass Energy card and a Lightning Energy card and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Togedemaru
flavorText: The long hairs on its back act as lightning rods. The bolts of lightning it attracts are stored as energy in its electric sac.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Discard all Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 30 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Zubat
flavorText: It sleeps in caves during the day. It has no eyes, so to check its surroundings while flying, it emits ultrasonic waves.
Attack1Text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

name: Golbat
flavorText: Its thick fangs are hollow like straws, making them unexpectedly fragile. These fangs are specialized for sucking blood.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Crobat
flavorText: Both its legs became wings, and as a result, it can't move well on the ground. All it can do is crawl around.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. Put 3 damage counters instead of 1 on that Pokémon between turns.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon was on the Bench and became your Active Pokémon this turn, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Alolan Grimer
flavorText: The crystals on Grimer's body are lumps of toxins. If one falls off, lethal poisons leak out.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Alolan Muk
flavorText: While it's unexpectedly quiet and friendly, if it's not fed any trash for a while, it will smash its Trainer's furnishings and eat up the fragments.
Ability1Text: Each Basic Pokémon in play, in each player's hand, and in each player's discard pile has no Abilities.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: It finds really fun dreams tasty. When it makes friends with people, it may show them the most delicious dreams it's ever eaten.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Hypno
flavorText: As a matter of course, it makes anyone it meets fall asleep and has a taste of their dreams. Anyone having a good dream, it carries off.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Espeon-GX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Mareanie
flavorText: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Toxapex
flavorText: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.
Ability1Text: Whenever your opponent's Active Pokémon retreats, their new Active Pokémon is Poisoned.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is Poisoned, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Cosmog
flavorText: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Cosmoem
flavorText: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Lunala-GX
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Psychic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't be healed during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Knock Out 1 of your opponent's Basic Pokémon that isn't a Pokémon-GX. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Makuhita
flavorText: It was originally brought in from another region, but now Makuhita from Alola are more famous.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Hariyama
flavorText: It is known for its fantastic strength, but as it grows older, it focuses more on training Makuhita.
Attack1Text: Your opponent switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Roggenrola
flavorText: The hexagonal cavity is its ear. It walks in the direction of sounds it hears, but if the sounds cease, it panics and topples over.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon has Fighting Resistance, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Boldore
flavorText: It explores caves in search of underground water. It's not comfortable around water, so this Pokémon takes great care in lapping it up.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Gigalith
flavorText: Known for its hefty horsepower, this Pokémon is a popular partner for construction workers.
Attack1Text: Discard any amount of Fighting Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 50 damage for each card you discarded in this way.
Attack2Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

name: Crabrawler
flavorText: It punches so much, its pincers often come off from overuse, but they grow back quickly. What little meat they contain is rich and delicious.

name: Passimian
flavorText: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkable—they will never let down a comrade.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Benched Passimian.

name: Sandygast
flavorText: It takes control of anyone who puts a hand in its mouth. And so it adds to the accumulation of its sand-mound body.
Attack1Text: Attach a Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.

name: Palossand
flavorText: Buried beneath the castle are masses of dried-up bones from those whose vitality it has drained.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 20 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Alolan Rattata
flavorText: When the sun goes down, it becomes active. It runs around town on a chase for good food for the boss of its nest—Raticate.

name: Alolan Raticate
flavorText: This gourmet Pokémon is particular about the taste and freshness of its food. Restaurants where Raticate live have a good reputation.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a number of cards up to the number of your Benched Pokémon and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Alolan Meowth
flavorText: This Pokémon was not originally found in Alola. Human actions caused a surge in their numbers, and they went feral. They're prideful and crafty.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

name: Alolan Persian
flavorText: Its round face and smooth coat—softer than the most high-class velvet—have made this a very popular Pokémon in Alola.
Attack1Text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Umbreon-GX
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Carvanha
flavorText: If they scent the faintest trace of blood, they rush to attack en masse. When alone, they're rather cowardly.
Attack1Text: Discard all Pokémon Tool cards from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Sharpedo
flavorText: It has a sad history. In the past, its dorsal fin was a treasured foodstuff, so this Pokémon became a victim of overfishing.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and is damaged by an opponent's attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

name: Sandile
flavorText: It submerges itself in sand and moves as if swimming. This wise behavior keeps its enemies from finding it and maintains its temperature.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Krokorok
flavorText: They move in groups of a few individuals. A female is often the leader of the group, and the males will gather food.
Attack1Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Krookodile
flavorText: Its unique faculty of sight can detect small prey more than 30 miles away, even in the midst of a sandstorm.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each card in your opponent's hand.
Attack2Text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tool cards from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Alolan Diglett
flavorText: Its head sports an altered form of whiskers made of metal. When in communication with its comrades, its whiskers wobble to and fro.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put them back in any order.

name: Alolan Dugtrio
flavorText: Its shining gold hair provides it with protection. It's reputed that keeping any of its fallen hairs will bring bad luck.
Ability1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost is Colorless more.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Skarmory
flavorText: Its feathers, which fall off as it grows, are thin and sharp. In times long past, warriors used them as swords.
Attack1Text: Discard all Special Energy from each Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Solgaleo-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for up to 5 Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Snubbull
flavorText: Its growls make its opponents uneasy. This laid-back Pokémon tends to sleep half the day.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this Pokémon does 10 damage to itself.

name: Granbull
flavorText: More timid than Snubbull, this Pokémon is doted on by young people amused at the contrast between its looks and its attitude.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Cutiefly
flavorText: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because it's able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.
Attack1Text: If any damage is done to this Pokémon by attacks during your opponent's next turn, flip a coin. If heads, prevent that damage.

name: Ribombee
flavorText: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Dratini
flavorText: After a 10-hour struggle, a fisherman was able to pull one up and confirm its existence.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Dratini, a Dragonair, and a Dragonite, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: From time immemorial, it has been venerated by agricultural peoples as an entity able to control the weather.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, you may attach any number of Energy cards from your hand to your Pokémon.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: Incur the wrath of this normally calm Pokémon at your peril, because it will smash everything to smithereens before it's satisfied.
Attack1Text: Discard a Grass Energy and a Lightning Energy from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Spearow
flavorText: Farmers whose fields are troubled by bug Pokémon appreciate Spearow for its vigorous appetite and look after it.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Grass Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Fearow
flavorText: Drawings of a Pokémon resembling Fearow can be seen in murals from deep in ancient history.
Attack1Text: Your opponent shuffles their hand into their deck and draws 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't use Slashing Strike during your next turn.

name: Kangaskhan
flavorText: Kangaskhan's maternal love is so deep that it will brave death to protect its offspring.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 30 more damage.
Attack2Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 50 damage for each heads.

name: Tauros-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.
Ability1Text: When you attach a basic Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon that is the same type as that Energy card and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, draw a card.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: Possessing an unbalanced and unstable genetic makeup, it conceals many possible evolutions.
Ability1Text: When you attach a basic Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon that is the same type as that Energy card and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, draw a card.

name: Spinda
flavorText: Its steps are staggering and unsteady, but Spinda thinks it's walking in a straight line.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Lillipup
flavorText: Because it doesn't yelp, it's extremely popular with Trainers who live in apartment buildings.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's attacks do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Herdier
flavorText: Its dense black fur grows continuously. The high cost of keeping its hard fur properly groomed make this a troublesome Pokémon to train.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may put an Item card from your discard pile into your hand.

name: Stoutland
flavorText: Intelligent, good-natured, and valiant, it's a trustworthy partner on rescue teams.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 50 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Pikipek
flavorText: This Pokémon feeds on berries, whose leftover seeds become the ammunition for the attacks it fires off from its mouth.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 10 more damage.

name: Trumbeak
flavorText: By bending its beak, it can produce a variety of call and brand itself a noisy nuisance for its neighbors.
Attack1Text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Toucannon
flavorText: Within its beak, its internal gas ignites, explosively launching seeds with enough power to pulverize boulders.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon's Echoed Voice attack does 60 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Yungoos
flavorText: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

name: Gumshoos-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may have your opponent reveal their hand.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Stufful
flavorText: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

name: Bewear
flavorText: This immensely dangerous Pokémon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't retreat during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: You may do 40 more damage. If you do, this Pokémon does 20 damage to itself.

name: Oranguru
flavorText: Deep in the jungle, high in the lofty canopy, this Pokémon abides. On rare occasions, it shows up at the beach to match wits with Slowking.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may draw cards until you have 3 cards in your hand.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Lurantis-GX
Attack1Text: Attach 2 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Lapras-GX
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon can't attack during your next turn.

name: Espeon-GX
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage times the amount of Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Lunala-GX
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a Psychic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
Attack1Text: The Defending Pokémon can't be healed during your opponent's next turn.
Attack2Text: Knock Out 1 of your opponent's Basic Pokémon that isn't a Pokémon-GX. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Umbreon-GX
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Solgaleo-GX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for up to 5 Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

name: Tauros-GX
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
